lass="containbox" style="margin:auto; position:relative; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom:20px; width:98%; background-color:var(--background-color);"><div style="float:left;"><a href="/about" class="p-author"><img class="ppic" src="https://shellsharks-images.s3.amazonaws.com/surfshark.png" width="60" alt="author-image" ></a></div><div style="float:left;"><span id="author" style="font-weight:bold;">Mike Sass</span><br><span id="handle" style="color:var(--light-font-color);">@shellsharks</span></div><div style="float:right;padding:10px 0px 0px 0px;"><i class="ph ph-calendar-dot"></i> <span id="date" style="font-size:0.75em;" class="dt-published">11/3/23 07:54</span></div><br><br><br><header id="header" class="post-header"></header><div class="post-content e-content"><p>I recently finished* my playthrough of Nintendo‚Äôs latest Mario side-scroller, <strong><a href="https://supermariobroswonder.nintendo.com">Super Mario Wonder</a></strong>. My short review? It was delightful but not without some deficiencies. I‚Äôve listed out <a href="#what-i-like">what I liked</a> and <a href="#what-i-didnt-like">what I didn‚Äôt like</a> below!<p>* <em>I haven‚Äôt yet conquered the final marathon level</em>.<h3 id="what-i-like">What I Like</h3><ul><li>The swappable <strong><a href="https://www.ign.com/wikis/super-mario-bros-wonder/List_of_Badges">badge</a></strong> system which grants your character a number of interesting abilities for the entirety of the level was great. Though I did tend to just default to the ‚ÄúBoosting Spin Jump‚Äù action badge as it gave me the most utility for avoiding death, getting top position on the flag pole, etc‚Ä¶<li>No surprise, but the art design, music and sound effects were all fantastic. Nintendo always shows up here.<li>Playing as a variety of characters is a great addition, though I tend to just play as Mario if all else is equal.<li>The ability to easily look at the progress for each (found) world and warp to it was a great quality-of-life feature.<li><a href="https://www.mariowiki.com/Wonder_Flower">Wonder Flowers</a> were a real joy. You honestly had no idea what would happen after triggering one and the overwhelming majority of wonder experiences were really great, a mix of challenging or simply rewardingly fun. My only complaint is that some of those individual experiences were so limited. Would have loved to reprise my role as the wondrous super <a href="https://www.mariowiki.com/Hoppycat">hoppy cat</a>.<li>Wonder introduced a whole slew of <a href="https://screenrant.com/super-mario-bros-wonder-every-new-enemy/">new kooky enemies</a>. <em>Loved ‚Äòem</em>.<li>In general, I thought the <a href="https://www.mariowiki.com/Super_Mario_Bros._Wonder#Levels">levels</a> were well-designed, of good length and very fun.</ul><h3 id="what-i-didnt-like">What I Didn‚Äôt Like</h3><ul><li>I know <em>why</em> they did it this way, but I would have liked it more had they made each character have a different, classic in-level ability. (i.e. <a href="https://www.mariowiki.com/Super_Mario_Bros._2#Characters">Super Mario 2</a>)<li>The new <a href="https://www.mariowiki.com/Super_Mario_Bros._Wonder#Power-ups">power-ups</a> (<a href="https://www.mariowiki.com/Drill_Mushroom">drill cap</a>, <a href="https://www.mariowiki.com/Elephant_Fruit">elephant fruit</a>, <a href="https://www.mariowiki.com/Bubble_Flower">bubble flower</a>) were only so-so for me. The drill might have been the best of the 3 but made certain things too easy and was too specific in other cases.<li>Any level that required me to jump to a beat. <em>Just no</em>. Seems somewhat exclusionary for deaf players or those who play with low/no sound.<li>Would have enjoyed more challenging levels.<li>There was not enough scarcity for the <a href="https://www.mariowiki.com/10-flower_coin">Purple Flower Coins</a> with respect to the currency system. Not that Mario should be about farming coins to buy stuff, but I <em>always</em> had enough coins to buy whatever I wanted, so it felt unncessary.<li>The game seemed short. Maybe it was just the fact that I binge played it, but between the relative easiness and the amount of <em>real</em> levels-of-substance, I felt it was just short. Some by-the-level comparisons below‚Ä¶<ul><li><a href="https://www.mariowiki.com/Super_Mario_Bros.#List_of_levels">Super Mario 1</a> - 32 levels<li><a href="https://www.mariowiki.com/Super_Mario_Bros._2#List_of_levels">Super Mario 2</a> - 20 levels - <a href="https://www.mariowiki.com/Super_Mario_Bros._3#Worlds">Super Mario 3</a> - 90 levels!<li><a href="https://www.mariowiki.com/Super_Mario_World#Worlds_and_levels">Super Mario World</a> - ~74 levels (though 96 unique exits)<li><a href="https://www.mariowiki.com/Super_Mario_World_2:_Yoshi%27s_Island#Worlds_and_levels">Super Mario Yoshi‚Äôs Island</a> - 54 levels<li><a href="https://www.mariowiki.com/Super_Mario_3D_World#Worlds">Super Mario 3D World</a> - 117 levels üëë<li><a href="https://www.mariowiki.com/Super_Mario_Bros._Wonder#Levels">Super Mario Wonder</a> - 152 levels, but only 79 of them are ‚Äúregular‚Äù levels, so not counting badge challenges, races, KO arenas, search parties or break times.</ul><li>There weren‚Äôt really a lot of boss battles, and the ones we did have were very one-note. No <a href="https://www.mariowiki.com/Reznor">Reznor‚Äôs</a>, no <a href="https://www.mariowiki.com/Big_Boo">Big Boo</a>, Bowser was just a floating hand thing (lame), no <a href="https://www.mariowiki.com/Magikoopa">Magikoopa</a>, no <a href="https://www.mariowiki.com/Boom_Boom">Boom Boom</a> <em>sigh</em>‚Ä¶<li>Not that many secrets (and secret exits), at least that I‚Äôve found.<li>What exactly was Bowser‚Äôs master plan? Just lulz? Other Mario games are relatively thin on ‚Äúplot‚Äù but Bowser has always been up to <em>something</em> - kidnapping Peach or really any type of kidnappings he does, conquering Mushroom Kingdom, etc‚Ä¶<li>Maybe it‚Äôs just nostalgia, but the map view is just not as exciting as <a href="https://www.mariouniverse.com/wp-content/img/maps/snes/smw/world-map-4.png">this classic</a>.</ul><hr /><h1 id="the-perfect-mario-game">The Perfect Mario Game</h1><p>Writing about what <a href="#what-i-like">I liked</a> and <a href="#what-i-didnt-like">didn‚Äôt like</a> about <a href="https://supermariobroswonder.nintendo.com">Super Mario Wonder</a> got me thinking. What would make for the <em>BEST</em> Super Mario game? (<em>Keeping this to just 2D side-scrolling</em>). I‚Äôve listed below the features I would want to see (with the game that first featured it in parentheses).<ul><li>Rideable Yoshi‚Äôs with different abilities. Dopamine hit every time I had that Blue Yoshi man‚Ä¶ (<a href="https://www.mariowiki.com/Super_Mario_World#Yoshis">Super Mario World</a>)<li>The <a href="https://www.mariowiki.com/P-Wing">P-Wing</a>. Yeah it‚Äôs a cheat code, but it was always fun deciding when to use it and being real nervous about messing it up. (Super Mario 3)<li>Characters with different native abilities. (<a href="https://www.mariowiki.com/Super_Mario_Bros._2#Characters">Super Mario 2</a>))<li>A more inspired world map. With lots of levels! (<a href="https://www.mariowiki.com/Super_Mario_World#Worlds_and_levels">Super Mario World</a>)<li>More secret exits (Super Mario World)<li>More difficult (Super Mario World-level difficulty)<li>More bosses! Both mini-bosses and world bosses. (Super Mario 3, Super Mario World)<li>Better power ups. Some of my favorites include <a href="https://www.mariowiki.com/Fire_Flower">fire flower</a> (of course), <a href="https://www.mariowiki.com/Super_Leaf">super leaf</a> (SM World), <a href="https://www.mariowiki.com/Hammer_Suit">hammer suit</a> (SM 3), <a href="https://www.mariowiki.com/Lucky_Bell">lucky bell</a> (the cat one from SM 3D World), <a href="https://www.mariowiki.com/Metal_Cap">metal cap</a> (SM 64), <a href="https://www.mariowiki.com/Tanooki_suit">Tanooki Suit</a> (SM 3), <a href="https://www.mariowiki.com/Wing_Cap">wing cap</a> (SM 64). Ya know what though? Just throw them <a href="https://www.mariowiki.com/List_of_power-ups">ALL IN</a> at once.<li>More ‚Äúmystery‚Äù. Super Mario 2 had this, ‚Äúwhat is happening, and where do I go‚Äù aspect that I remember so fondly.<li>More bonus levels. Super Mario 3D World bonus levels just kept going and going.<li>Multi-player. (Pretty much standard at this point).<li>Star system for unlocking new parts of the world and new levels (Super Mario 64, Wonder had something similar-ish with the Wonder Seeds.)<li>Per-level challenge system. (<a href="https://www.mariowiki.com/Super_Mario_64#Courses">Super Mario 64</a> had 6 challenges per level)<li>Plot-wise, I really enjoyed what Super Mario RPG did. Let <a href="https://www.mariowiki.com/Super_Mario_RPG:_Legend_of_the_Seven_Stars#Bowser">Bowser</a> be a good guy (and playable) and introduce a new team of big-bads. In fact, RPG had the best story by a mile, remember Bowser‚Äôs character arc? So good.<li><a href="https://www.mariowiki.com/Wonder_Flower">Wonder Flowers</a> were a TON of fun. Would love to see this mechanic tweaked a bit though for more replayability. Like initiating wonder flower effects from one level in a completely different level. Like‚Ä¶ the wonder flower effect could be randomized such that hitting one could cause a completely different effect in the level each time you hit it. <em>Amazing‚Ä¶</em><li>Currency-system wise, do what Super Mario RPG did with <a href="https://www.mariowiki.com/Frog_Coin">frog coins</a>. Imagine being able to buy unique power-ups, wonder-flower effects, badge-effects, etc with a currency that wasn‚Äôt so easiliy farmed? Could be fun.<li>I don‚Äôt know how this gets incorporated, but I would love to see <a href="https://www.mariowiki.com/Super_Mario_Kart">Mario Kart</a> somehow baked into a standard Super Mario platformer, as a mini-game or something.<li>I like all the per-level find-all-the-things challenges. <a href="https://www.mariowiki.com/Red_Coin">Red coins</a>, purple flower coins, stars, special flowers, all of ‚Äòem.<li>Yoshi throwing eggs. (<a href="https://www.mariowiki.com/Super_Mario_World_2:_Yoshi%27s_Island#Playable_characters">Super Mario Yoshi‚Äôs Island</a>)</ul><p>Please make this Nintendo!!!</div><div style="bottom:-5px; text-align:right;font-size:0.75em;"><i class="ph ph-pencil"></i> 1127</div><hr style="opacity:35%;margin-top: 10px;margin-bottom: 10px;width:75%;"><div id="info" class="wrapper"><div class="box 1" style="background-color:var(--background-color);"><div><i class="ph ph-map-pin-area" title="Posted from"></i> <span id="posted-from" style="font-size:0.75em;">iPad Pro</span></div><div><i class="ph ph-broadcast"></i><span style="font-size:0.75em;"> Syndication:</span></div><div style="font-size:1.5em;"><span id="syndicate-to"> <span style="padding:0px 3px 0px 3px;"><a href="https://infosec.exchange/@shellsharks/111346519518897124"><i class="ph ph-mastodon-logo" title="Mastodon"></i></a></span> <span style="padding:0px 3px 0px 3px;"><a href="https://www.threads.net/@mk3s/post/CzLuqaYLel-/"><i class="ph ph-threads-logo" title="Threads"></i></a></span> </span></div></div><div class="box2" style="bottom:0;"><div style="text-align:right; padding:5px 5px 5px 5px;"><a class="u-url" href=""><i class="ph ph-link" title="Permalink"></i></a> <a href="/notebook"><i class="ph ph-book-open" title="Notebook"></i></a> <a href="/"><i class="ph ph-house" title="Home"></i></a></div><div style="font-size:0.75em;color:var(--light-font-color);padding:5px 5px 0px 5px;text-align:right;"><i class="ph ph-tag"></i> <span id="tags" style="padding:0px 3px 0px 3px;"><a href="/tags?tag=nablopomo">#nablopomo</a></span> <span id="tags" style="padding:0px 3px 0px 3px;"><a href="/tags?tag=gaming">#gaming</a></span> <span id="tags" style="padding:0px 3px 0px 3px;"><a href="/tags?tag=mario">#mario</a></span> <span id="tags" style="padding:0px 3px 0px 3px;"><a href="/tags?tag=nintendo">#nintendo</a></span></div></div></d